# pikiloom-skills — shared local secrets
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to  ~/.pikiloom/skills.env  and fill in only the keys you need.
#
#   cp .env.example ~/.pikiloom/skills.env && chmod 600 ~/.pikiloom/skills.env
#
# Every skill resolves a key in this order (first hit wins):
#   CLI flag  →  process env  →  skill-specific *_ENV_FILE  →  ~/.pikiloom/skills.env
#
# NEVER commit the filled-in file. The repo's .gitignore drops *.env on purpose.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── image-gen ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Use a DIRECT OpenAI key (sk-... / sk-svcacct-...), NOT an OpenRouter key:
# OpenRouter blocks OpenAI image models (gpt-image-*) by data policy.
OPENAI_API_KEY=
# Optional: override the OpenAI-compatible base URL (proxy / gateway).
# OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1

# ── video-use ── voiceover TTS (OPTIONAL — subtitles need zero keys) ──────────
# OpenRouter key for gpt-audio voiceover; without it use `--engine say` (macOS).
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=
# Optional login for the page-tour recorder (keeps creds out of `ps`):
# RECORD_WEB_EMAIL=
# RECORD_WEB_PASSWORD=
# Optional, ONLY for word-level editing of spoken-source footage (upstream tool):
# ELEVENLABS_API_KEY=

# ── discover ── embeddable signal pipeline ───────────────────────────────────
# LLM draft step reuses OPENROUTER_API_KEY above.
# Feishu publisher adapter (only needed if you wire the Feishu sink):
FEISHU_APP_ID=
FEISHU_APP_SECRET=
FEISHU_RECEIVE_ID=
